-- Reliance Builds Indonesia Rail Lines to Move Coal, Standard Says
-- B y   A d i   N a r a y a n
-- 2010-09-26T05:38:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-26/reliance-builds-indonesia-rail-lines-to-move-coal-to-ports-standard-says.html
Reliance Power Ltd., is speeding up
the construction of railway lines from coal mines to ports in
Indonesia’s South Sumatra region, the Business Standard
reported, citing an unidentified official at the Indian company.  Coal from the mines, which are owned by a Reliance
subsidiary, is meant for the company’s proposed power plant in
Krishnapatnam town, southern India.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Adi Narayan in Mumbai at 
 anarayan8@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
